For this problem, we will use the concept of the future value of annuity which is basically the future value of the recurring payments to be done in the future based on the given rates. It can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Future value annuity}&=\text{Cash flow} \times \dfrac{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}-1}{\text{rate}}
\end{aligned}$$

Now to solve for the lump sump investment needed to equal Investment A, we will use the formula for the present value:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value}&=\dfrac{\text{Cash flow}}{(1+\text{rate})^\text{time}}
\end{aligned}$$
